    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Opening Day for Sale</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Rita Lynch letter on Mar 21 article endorses Mark McGwire's criticism of Major League Baseball for holding opening day in Japan</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>I totally agree with Mark McGwire's comments in ''McGwire Criticizes the Opener in Japan and Cites Greed'' (March 21). When will Major League Baseball stop prostituting America's pastime? And it's a slap in the face to loyal Met and Cub fans who look forward to opening day in either hometown.</p>
        <p>RITA LYNCH  New York</p>
      </block>
